->>> SIMPLEGAUGE_METHODS
@node SIMPLEGAUGE_METHODS "New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link SIMPLEGAUGE_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF sg:PTR TO simplegauge_plugin
      ...
      NEW sg.simplegauge([..., TAG_DONE])
      ...
      sg.set(PLA_Simplegauge_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link SIMPLEGAUGE_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=sg.get(PLA_Simplegauge_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

      But if you try:

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=sg.get(PLA_SimpleGauge_ShowText)
      ...@{FG text}

      Then you get this:
       value:=-1
       check:=FALSE


   @{b}draw()@{ub}              @{FG shine}@{i}/* Private */@{ui}@{FG text}


@endnode
-><<

->>> SIMPLEGAUGE_TAGS
@node SIMPLEGAUGE_TAGS "Tags"
 The letters [ISG] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link SIMPLEGAUGE_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link SIMPLEGAUGE_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link SIMPLEGAUGE_METHODS 18}


   @{FG shine}PLA_Simplegauge_Disabled@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Disable or enable a gadget. Setting this tag causes the
      gadget to become disabled, it gets a ghost pattern.


   @{FG shine}PLA_Simplegauge_Current@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Set the current level of the gauge. The value must be
      between 0 and PLA_Simplegauge_Max.
      If it's not it will be fit to this bounds.
      Default is 0.


   @{FG shine}PLA_Simplegauge_Max@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Set the maximum value for the gauge.
      Default is 100.


   @{FG shine}PLA_SimpleGauge_Horizontal@{FG text}  [I.G]

      Determine if you want a horizontal or vertical gauge.
      Default is FALSE.


   @{FG shine}PLA_SimpleGauge_Percent@{FG text}  [..G]

      Use this tag to get the current percentage of the gauge.


   @{FG shine}PLA_SimpleGauge_ShowText@{FG text}  [I..]

      Determine if you want to show the percentage of the gauge.


   @{FG shine}PLA_SimpleGauge_BackgroundPen@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Use this tag to set the backgound color of your gauge.


   @{FG shine}PLA_SimpleGauge_BarPen@{FG text}  [ISG]

      This tag set the color of the bar.

@endnode
